Package gg.xp.xivsupport.events.actlines.events

Class LimitBreakGaugeEvent

java.lang.Object
gg.xp.reevent.events.BaseEvent
gg.xp.xivsupport.events.actlines.events.LimitBreakGaugeEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Event, HasPrimaryValue, Serializable
public class LimitBreakGaugeEvent extends BaseEvent implements HasPrimaryValue
Represents an LB gauge update.

Please make sure you are handling things correctly when there is no LB available in the duty. See isLbAvailable()

    • getTotalBars

      public int getTotalBars()
      Returns:
      The number of possible bars. e.g. 3 bars in a raid. Not affected by how many bars are full.

    • getMaxRawValue

      public int getMaxRawValue()
      Returns:
      The maximum for getCurrentRawValue() as determined by getTotalBars().

    • getCurrentRawValue

      public int getCurrentRawValue()
      Returns:
      The raw amount of the LB gauge, as an integer. Each 10,000 increment is one bar.
      See Also:
      • PER_BAR

    • getCurrentValue

      public float getCurrentValue()
      Returns:
      The current LB gauge state as a float. Equivalent to getCurrentRawValue() / PER_BAR (floating point division).

    • getFullBars

      public int getFullBars()
      Returns:
      the number of completely full bars.

    • isEmpty

      public boolean isEmpty()
      Returns:
      whether the LB gauge is empty. If no LB is available in the duty, always returns true.

    • isFull

      public boolean isFull()
      Returns:
      whether the LB guage is full. If no LB is available in the duty, always returns true.

    • isLbUsable

      public boolean isLbUsable()
      Returns:
      whether LB is currently usable, i.e. at least one complete LB bar is full.

    • isLbAvailable

      public boolean isLbAvailable()
      Returns:
      whether there is any LB bar whatsoever, regardless of current state. i.e. whether the current duty and party size supports LBs.
